        "644": {
          "vnum": 644,
          "name": "A Mossy Hollow",
          "description": "Invisible from the other side of this hill, a strange depression in the hillside has created here a vast hollow. A backbone of bedrock to the west curves above and around you, the resulting windbreak allowing trees to flourish densely, their trunks covered in blue-green moss. This oasis of life manages to make the surrounding plains seem a desert in comparison.",
